CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 3, 1945, pg. 5, reads: "Bible Class Dinner - The Queen Esther Bible class of the Calvary Baptist Church was entertained at dinner at the YMCA recently. The dinner was given by the class teacher, William L. Jordan. Miss Dorothy Guinn, executive secretary of the YWCA, was the principal after dinner speaker. Other after dinner speakers were the Rev. J. O. Williams, Mrs. Martin, William Matthews, Mrs. D. Ross and Mrs. K. Jordan of Duquesne, Pa. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Calvary Baptist Church Queen Esther Bible class members and speakers, possibly including William L. Jordan, Dorothy Guinn, Rev. J. O. Williams, Mrs. Martin, William Matthews, Mrs. D. Ross and Mrs. K. Jordan gathered for dinner in YMCA
